"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Replace combinatorial wrapper types with CapabilityDeclarer pattern\n\n## Context\n\nThe `Wrap()` function in `external/capabilities.go` manually defines wrapper types for each combination of capabilities an external agent can declare. With 7 capability flags, this doesn't scale (128 possible combinations; currently only 9 are covered). The fix: introduce a `CapabilityDeclarer` interface and `As*` helper functions so a single wrapper type can implement all interfaces, with capability gating done at the call site via helpers.\n\nBuilt-in agents are unaffected — they don't implement `CapabilityDeclarer`, so the helpers fall through to direct type assertions.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### 1. Create `cmd/entire/cli/agent/capabilities.go` (new file)\n\nDefine:\n- `CapabilityDeclarer` interface with `DeclaredCapabilities() DeclaredCaps`\n- `DeclaredCaps` struct (7 bool fields matching `external.Capabilities`)\n- 7 helper functions: `AsHookSupport`, `AsTranscriptAnalyzer`, `AsTranscriptPreparer`, `AsTokenCalculator`, `AsTextGenerator`, `AsHookResponseWriter`, `AsSubagentAwareExtractor`\n\nEach helper:\n```go\nfunc AsHookSupport(ag Agent) (HookSupport, bool) {\n    hs, ok := ag.(HookSupport)\n    if !ok { return nil, false }\n    if cd, ok := ag.(CapabilityDeclarer); ok {\n        return hs, cd.DeclaredCapabilities().Hooks\n    }\n    return hs, true\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Create `cmd/entire/cli/agent/capabilities_test.go` (new file)\n\nTest each helper with 4 scenarios:\n1. Mock agent NOT implementing the interface → `false`\n2. Mock built-in agent implementing the interface (no `CapabilityDeclarer`) → `true`\n3. Mock agent with `CapabilityDeclarer` + capability=`true` → `true`\n4. Mock agent with `CapabilityDeclarer` + capability=`false` → `false`\n\n### 3. Rewrite `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/capabilities.go`\n\nReplace all 9 wrapper types (`baseAgent`, `hooksAgent`, `analyzerAgent`, `preparerAgent`, `analyzerPreparerAgent`, `hooksPreparerAgent`, `hooksAnalyzerPreparerAgent`, `hooksAnalyzerAgent`, `fullAgent`) with a single `wrappedAgent` that:\n- Forwards all `agent.Agent` methods to `ea`\n- Implements ALL optional interface methods (forwarding to `ea`)\n- Implements `CapabilityDeclarer`, returning caps converted from `ea.info.Capabilities`\n\n`Wrap()` becomes:\n```go\nfunc Wrap(ea *Agent) agent.Agent {\n    caps := ea.info.Capabilities\n    return &wrappedAgent{\n        ea: ea,\n        caps: agent.DeclaredCaps{\n            Hooks:                  caps.Hooks,\n            TranscriptAnalyzer:     caps.TranscriptAnalyzer,\n            TranscriptPreparer:     caps.TranscriptPreparer,\n            TokenCalculator:        caps.TokenCalculator,\n            TextGenerator:          caps.TextGenerator,\n            HookResponseWriter:     caps.HookResponseWriter,\n            SubagentAwareExtractor: caps.SubagentAwareExtractor,\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Update call sites (mechanical — 22 production sites)\n\nReplace `ag.(agent.X)` with `agent.AsX(ag)`:\n\n| File | Sites | Interfaces |\n|------|-------|-----------|\n| `setup.go` | 5 | HookSupport |\n| `lifecycle.go` | 5 | HookResponseWriter, TranscriptPreparer, TranscriptAnalyzer, SubagentAwareExtractor |\n| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | 4 | TranscriptPreparer, TranscriptAnalyzer |\n| `agent/token_usage.go` | 2 | SubagentAwareExtractor, TokenCalculator (no `agent.` prefix — same package) |\n| `config.go` | 1 | HookSupport |\n| `hook_registry.go` | 1 | HookSupport |\n| `hooks_cmd.go` | 1 | HookSupport |\n| `state.go` | 1 | TranscriptAnalyzer |\n| `strategy/common.go` | 1 | TranscriptPreparer |\n| `setup_test.go` | 2 | HookSupport |\n\n### 5. Update `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go`\n\nChange all direct type assertions (`wrapped.(agent.HookSupport)`) to use `agent.AsHookSupport(wrapped)` etc. The wrapped agent now always satisfies all interfaces — correctness is gated by the `As*` helpers.\n\n### 6. Update integration tests (`integration_test/agent_test.go`) — ~15 sites\n\nThese use built-in agents, so they'll work either way. Update for consistency: `agent.AsHookSupport(ag)` instead of `ag.(agent.HookSupport)`.\n\n## Files Modified\n\n- **New:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/capabilities.go`\n- **New:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/capabilities_test.go`\n- **Rewritten:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/capabilities.go`\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go`\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/token_usage.go` (2 sites)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` (5 sites)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` (5 sites)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (4 sites)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (1 site)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/config.go` (1 site)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` (1 site)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` (1 site)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/state.go` (1 site)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go` (2 sites)\n- **Edited:** `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/agent_test.go` (~15 sites)\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/nodo/.claude/projects/-Users-nodo-work-cli/323f78c7-a406-44fa-bc2f-8aef24edceec.jsonl"